<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="303" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph box="[112,821,435,479]" pageId="24" pageNumber="303" type="mainText">
Habitat &amp; Ecology - Few data. Reported from lowlands to high elevations (
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="24" pageNumber="303" unit="m" value="1400.0" valueMax="2500.0" valueMin="300.0">
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="24" pageNumber="303" unit="m" value="1400.0" valueMax="2500.0" valueMin="300.0">300- 2500 m),</quantity>
</quantity>
in forest and in severely disturbed areas, epiphytic or terrestrial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="303" type="discussion">
<paragraph box="[112,821,484,601]" pageId="24" pageNumber="303" type="mainText">
Note - Similar in pinna shape and position of the sori to 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Nephrolepidaceae" genus="Nephrolepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="24" pageNumber="303" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="falciformis">N. falciformis</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the very dark, dense, squarrose rachis scales; the denser and more persistent lamina scales, and the absence of hairs on the costae. Juvenile specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kunze - Fig" authorityYear="1846" baseAuthorityName="Sw." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Nephrolepidaceae" genus="Nephrolepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="24" pageNumber="303" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davallioides">N. davallioides</taxonomicName>
may have a similar rachis indument and may then be impossible to distinguish from sterile fronds of 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Nephrolepidaceae" genus="Nephrolepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="24" pageNumber="303" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="falcata">N. falcata</taxonomicName>
<authority>
<authority>
<authority>.</authority>
</authority>
</authority>
</paragraph>
